/* However, the mismatch also affects the THETA equation.
   Variation of V_conf = (gamma/2)|M|^2 |phi|^2 with respect to theta_a:
   dV/dtheta_a = (gamma/2) |phi|^2 d|M|^2/dtheta_a
               = (gamma/2) |phi|^2 * 2 M_b * dM_b/dtheta_a
               = (gamma/2) |phi|^2 * 2 M_a * (-1)
               = -gamma |phi|^2 M_a
               = -gamma |phi|^2 (curl(phi)/2 - theta)_a

   In the theta equation: F_theta = ... + gamma |phi_0|^2 (curl(phi_0)/2 - theta)
   For theta fluctuations around theta_0:
   F_theta(delta) = ... + gamma |phi_0|^2 (-delta_theta)

   Effective theta mass: m_th_eff^2 = gamma |phi_0(x)|^2 */

print("Theta equation from mismatch potential:")$
