   For A_bg = 0.1 and wavelength = 2pi/k where k ~ m = 1.5:
   |curl(phi_bg)| ~ A_bg * k = 0.15
   |M_bg| ~ |curl(phi_bg)/2| = 0.075 (if theta_bg = 0)
   |M_bg|^2 ~ 0.006 */

M_sq_bg: 0.006$
print("Background mismatch (if theta_bg = 0):")$
print("  |curl(phi_bg)/2|^2 ~ ", M_sq_bg)$
print("  Phi exterior mass: m_eff^2 = 2.25 + gamma * ", M_sq_bg)$
print("  For m_eff > 3: gamma * 0.006 > 6.75")$
gamma_needed_phi: 6.75 / M_sq_bg;
print("  gamma > ", float(gamma_needed_phi))$
print("")$

/* gamma ~ 1000 is very large. But let's check self-consistency. */
